verdict.similar_deals:
Growth equity investment in 'OrthoDynamics' (2023), a surgical robotics firm with similar late-stage pilots but yet to achieve profitability; 
Add-on acquisition of 'BioSurg Analytics' by a PE-backed medtech platform in 2024 for its proprietary surgical outcome analytics; 
Series C funding of 'RoboSpine' in 2025, a competitor targeting spine surgery robotics with both upstream technology and downstream software licensing; 
Private equity participation in 'AssistMed' 2022 buyout specializing in consumables for robotic surgical systems, with stable recurring revenue streams.

verdict.key_information_requested:
Detailed customer contracts and renewal rates to assess stickiness; 
Surgeon and hospital feedback on NexuArm usability and clinical outcomes versus competitors; 
Breakdown of product cost structure to evaluate margin improvement potential;
Near-term sales pipeline visibility and signed purchase agreements;
Regulatory approval status and timelines for expansion markets;
Detailed roadmap and expected capital requirements to reach profitability; 
Competitive intelligence on market share movements and pricing dynamics.
